00:34:18,650 --> 00:34:20,492
of how systemic or narrative system was.

818
00:34:20,733 --> 00:34:21,994
So to explain that.

819
00:34:23,718 --> 00:34:25,739
If you were a lizard and you talk to people,

820
00:34:25,779 --> 00:34:27,480
they talk to you as if you were a lizard.

821
00:34:27,680 --> 00:34:29,640
If you were an undead, they freak the hell out

822
00:34:30,381 --> 00:34:31,421
if they were afraid of undead,

823
00:34:31,481 --> 00:34:33,342
and so we had to have different behavior.

824
00:34:34,002 --> 00:34:36,643
The idea was that you were going to be able to handle this

825
00:34:36,683 --> 00:34:38,364
because you would have a mask of the shapeshifters.

826
00:34:38,404 --> 00:34:39,704
The mask of the shapeshifter was cool

827
00:34:39,744 --> 00:34:41,025
because it changed your tags,

828
00:34:41,305 --> 00:34:43,005
and it showcased that if you changed tags,

829
00:34:43,065 --> 00:34:45,066
the dialogs changed, so they rotated.

830
00:34:45,486 --> 00:34:46,827
We thought it was a very awesome feature

831
00:34:46,847 --> 00:34:48,668
because it showed exactly how deep the game was,

832
00:34:48,728 --> 00:34:50,268
and we absolutely wanted to have it in there.

833
00:34:51,029 --> 00:34:52,610
One thing that we hadn't thought of was that

834
00:34:53,330 --> 00:34:55,372
if you were an undead and there's jokes

