00:37:09,343 --> 00:37:10,344
And then he asked me,

878
00:37:10,504 --> 00:37:12,606
how do I do this voice recording pipeline?

879
00:37:12,686 --> 00:37:14,067
Because he didn't want to go to the producer.

880
00:37:14,568 --> 00:37:16,724
and that the script had changed.

881
00:37:18,456 --> 00:37:22,598
So now imagine, yeah, so now I have this slide here

882
00:37:22,638 --> 00:37:25,080
because the producers deserve a lot of respect

883
00:37:25,580 --> 00:37:30,263
for despite being grumpy and deservedly angry at us,

884
00:37:31,043 --> 00:37:33,164
they did cover us at every single moment in time.

885
00:37:33,184 --> 00:37:34,525
They made sure that everything worked.

886
00:37:34,565 --> 00:37:36,346
They figured out solutions for all of the problems

887
00:37:36,366 --> 00:37:37,187
that we encountered.

888
00:37:37,887 --> 00:37:40,648
And you can for sure say that without them,

889
00:37:40,809 --> 00:37:42,470
nothing was going to happen.

890
00:37:42,530 --> 00:37:44,371
It would have been one gigantic mess.

891
00:37:45,111 --> 00:37:47,053
Now imagine that you're working at Larian Studios

892
00:37:47,093 --> 00:37:48,094
and you're working in QA.

