00:39:41,482 --> 00:39:43,883
one seven out of 10 from Polygon, rightfully so,

943
00:39:44,043 --> 00:39:45,924
because she was on a, yeah,

944
00:39:45,944 --> 00:39:48,945
she had a really lots of problems in her questing,

945
00:39:49,025 --> 00:39:51,807
and that was actually a result of all of these changes.

946
00:39:51,847 --> 00:39:53,447
So it's not something that I would recommend.

947
00:39:54,068 --> 00:39:56,889
On the other hand, if we wouldn't have done it,

948
00:39:57,369 --> 00:39:58,530
then the game wouldn't have been as good

949
00:39:58,670 --> 00:40:00,591
and as well received as it was.

950
00:40:01,971 --> 00:40:09,264
So there was more going on than just a story, but story was probably the biggest thing that

951
00:40:09,284 --> 00:40:12,449
went wrong during Original Sin 2. That's why I spent so much time talking about it.

952
00:40:13,291 --> 00:40:14,553
We also wanted to improve combat.

953
00:40:15,605 --> 00:40:19,770
And so we wanted to improve multiple mechanics.

954
00:40:20,230 --> 00:40:22,592
And so we decided that the armor system should be better.

955
00:40:23,513 --> 00:40:25,856
And we were very enthusiastic about it, because we tested it.

956
00:40:25,936 --> 00:40:26,957
We tested it at PAX.

957
00:40:27,397 --> 00:40:29,820
And we saw that people instantly got how armor worked.

958
00:40:29,960 --> 00:40:31,261
And it was very intuitive to them.

959
00:40:31,982 --> 00:40:34,824
And so we were very enthusiastic when we launched it

