1385
00:58:48,449 --> 00:58:50,990
We're not really focused on the min-maxing.

1386
00:58:51,030 --> 00:58:52,951
We think about a game as something

1387
00:58:52,971 --> 00:58:54,152
in which you should have fun,

1388
00:58:54,252 --> 00:58:56,253
especially if you're playing in cooperative multiplayer,

1389
00:58:56,293 --> 00:58:57,874
which is where most of these cases appear.

1390
00:58:58,654 --> 00:58:59,435
You just wanna play,

1391
00:58:59,895 --> 00:59:01,415
like you were playing Dungeons and Dragons, you know?

1392
00:59:01,516 --> 00:59:03,056
You're playing a pen and paper session.

1393
00:59:03,296 --> 00:59:04,097
You're goofing around.

1394
00:59:04,137 --> 00:59:04,957
You're having a lot of fun.

1395
00:59:04,977 --> 00:59:06,338
There's reasons to continue in the world.

1396
00:59:06,758 --> 00:59:08,379
And that, I think, is the most important bit

1397
00:59:08,419 --> 00:59:09,319
about RPG design.

